explanation: This solution uses dynamic programming to build a 2D table dp where dp[i][j] represents the minimum number of changes needed to make the substring s[i..j] a palindrome. Then it uses another dynamic programming table dp2 to find the minimum number of changes needed to divide the string into k palindromic substrings.

